Abuja (Sundiata Post) – President Muhammadu Buhari has nominated the Acting Chief Justice of Nigeria (CJN), Justice Tanko Mohammed as substantive CJN. Recall that President Buhari picked Justice Tanko to take over from the former Chief Justice of Nigeria Justice Walter Onnoghen after he was forced to step aside over alleged non- declaration of assets to the Code of Conduct Bureau (CCB) as required by law for all public officers. Details Later…